## Conversation
User (atruong, weave-trace owner): "Our Agents OTEL endpoint is a bit loose
atm. We don't enforce that the trace requires a certain shape. Please
investigate what shape is enforced today and help me tighten this constraint.
The goal is to ensure that data that ends up in our DB is an expected shape. If
spans show up in the database that are not expected, we should warn the user
what the problem is (and ideally provide a way for them to improve their code).
Optionally the server can reject the span." Also prefixed with "Use no-mistakes."

Interpreted as: warn-by-default (surface actionable guidance), opt-in reject.
The "Optionally the server can reject" phrasing drove the warn-default +
env-gated-strict design (non-breaking rollout).

