2. Consulted Codex (thread 019ef4aa) on the design. Key adopted feedback:
   - Post-extraction loses PRESENCE: a real gen_ai.usage.input_tokens=0 looks
     identical to absence in the row. So the junk gate must read the ORIGINAL
     span's attribute KEYS, not the extracted row's values.
   - Do NOT count borrowed generic OTel keys (server.address, error.type,
     server.port are in KNOWN_KEYS!) as GenAI signal -> use namespace prefixes
     gen_ai./weave. instead. A plain HTTP span has server.address.
   - Cut warned_spans response field (no consumer; error_message already
     carries it). Keep response schema unchanged.
   - Aggregate by code, not per-span prose. Catalog (code->severity/message/
     remediation) instead of rich per-instance objects.
   - warn-default + opt-in reject is right for an ingest compatibility change.
