## Codebase Discoveries
- KNOWN_KEYS (semconv.py) includes non-gen_ai aliases: error.type,
  server.address, server.port. So it is NOT a safe 'is this GenAI' signal.
- After unflatten_key_values, dotted attr keys nest under a top-level root
  ('gen_ai', 'weave'); flat dotted form also possible. span_claims_genai handles
  both (root membership + dotted prefix).
- Span.from_proto builds trace_id/span_id via hexlify(bytes); all-zero bytes ->
  all-'0' hex (not empty). _is_blank_id treats empty AND all-zero as missing.

